# NAS Mount Configuration for VM Template
# This file shows the NAS mounts to be included in the VM template
#
# NAS Server: 192.168.86.43
# Protocol: CIFS (Samba/Windows shares)
# Authentication: Username/password (stored in fstab - consider keyring in future)
#
# IMPORTANT: Replace {{ nas_username }} and {{ nas_password }} with actual credentials
# These will be managed by Ansible variables

# Media share - for video content
//192.168.86.43/media           /mnt/video      cifs    username={{ nas_username }},password={{ nas_password }},vers=2.0,rw,file_mode=0777,dir_mode=0777,nofail   0       0

# Complete share - for completed downloads
//192.168.86.43/complete        /mnt/complete   cifs    username={{ nas_username }},password={{ nas_password }},vers=2.0,rw,file_mode=0777,dir_mode=0777,nofail   0       0

# Music share - for music content
//192.168.86.43/music           /mnt/music      cifs    username={{ nas_username }},password={{ nas_password }},vers=2.0,rw,file_mode=0777,dir_mode=0777,nofail   0       0

# Notes:
# - vers=2.0: SMB protocol version
# - rw: Read-write access
# - file_mode=0777,dir_mode=0777: Full permissions (consider restricting in future)
# - nofail: Don't prevent boot if NAS is unavailable
#
# Post-clone customization:
# - Some VMs may not need all mounts (e.g., VM 103 doesn't use /mnt/complete)
# - Use customize-vm-clone.sh script to disable unneeded mounts
#
# Security consideration:
# - Credentials in plain text in fstab
# - Acceptable for local network
# - Future: Consider using credentials file or keyring
